transcript: My English teacher in high school used to show old films, then ask the females in the class to sit on his lap in the back of the class while he edited our work. Almost every girl in the class did this, so it seemed like the norm, until I told my older sister who said, “What?” I spoke to the teacher, then the principal, then the superintendent. Only one other girl join me in our complaint. My parents were out of town so I went with the other student and her father to the superintendent who kept questioning our memory. The only thing they did was pull his application for “Teacher of the Year.” He won it the following year.
